SIMPLE: okra
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Okra
<hw>O"kra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>An annual plant (<spn>Abelmoschus esculentus</spn> syn.
<spn>Hibiscus esculentus</spn>), whose green pods, abounding in
nutritious mucilage, are much used for soups, stews, or pickles;
gumbo.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>ocra</asp> and
<asp>ochra</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The pods of the plant okra, used as a vegetable;
also, a dish prepared with them; gumbo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1000 --></p>

<p><ent>-ol</ent>⟦br⟧
